tr.td: The patient shows low HbA1c, likely reflecting absence of diabetes or possible hypoglycemia. Renal and electrolyte parameters are within normal limits. Lipid profile reveals elevated total and LDL cholesterol and low HDL cholesterol, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of lipid-lowering therapy and lifestyle modification.
